First Read: 21-Jan-26
SB194 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to ethics, to amend Section 36-25-15, Code of
5 Alabama 1975, to eliminate a requirement that a candidate who
6 has already filed a statement of economic interests notify the
7 State Ethics Commission of this fact.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
9 Section 1. Section 36-25-15, Code of Alabama 1975, as
10 last amended by Act 2025-282 of the 2025 Regular Session, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 "§36-25-15
13 (a) Candidates at every level of government shall file
14 a completed statement of economic interests for the previous
15 calendar year with the State Ethics Commission: (i) not more
16 than five days after the deadline to file a declaration of
17 candidacy as provided in Section 17-13-5, or in the case of an
18 independent candidate, not more than five days after the date
19 of the first primary election; or (ii) for a candidate for
20 municipal office, not more than five days after the deadline
21 for the candidate to file his or her qualifying papers with
22 the appropriate election official. Nothing in this section
23 shall be deemed to require a second filing of the individual's
24 statement of economic interests if a current statement of
25 economic interests is on file with the commission. If a
26 candidate has already filed a current statement of economic
27 interests for a reason other than his or her candidacy, the
28 candidate, by the deadline provided by this subsection, shall
Page 1

candidate, by the deadline provided by this subsection, shall
SB194 Enrolled
29 provide proof to the commission that a current statement has
30 already been submitted or file a new or amended statement.
31 (b) Each election official who receives a declaration
32 of candidacy or petition to appear on the ballot for election
33 from a candidate, within five days of the receipt, shall
34 notify the commission of the name of the candidate, as defined
35 in this chapter, and the date on which the individual became a
36 candidate. The commission, within five business days of the
37 filing deadline described in subsection (a), shall notify the
38 election official whether the candidate has complied with this
39 section. If the commission's notification indicates the
40 candidate has not complied with this section, the election
41 official shall immediately notify the candidate, and the
42 candidate shall have five additional days to provide evidence
43 to the election official that the candidate has filed a
44 statement of economic interests in compliance with this
45 section.
46 (c) Other provisions of the law notwithstanding, if a
47 candidate does not submit a statement of economic interests or
48 when applicable, an amended statement of economic interests in
49 accordance with the requirements of this chapter, the name of
50 the individual shall not appear on the ballot and the
51 candidate shall be deemed not qualified as a candidate in that
52 election. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the commission, for
53 good cause shown, may allow the candidate an additional five
54 days to file the statement of economic interests. If a
55 candidate is deemed not qualified, the appropriate election
56 official shall remove the name of the candidate from the
Page 2

official shall remove the name of the candidate from the
SB194 Enrolled
57 ballot."
58 Section 2. This act shall become effective immediately.
Page 3

